# Hawkeye Sterling — Trivy vulnerability exceptions
#
# CVEs listed here are known vulnerabilities that have been evaluated and
# confirmed NOT exploitable in our deployment context. Each entry must include:
#   - CVE identifier
#   - Package affected
#   - Reason it is not exploitable here
#   - Review date and reviewer
#   - Next review date (max 12 months)
#
# Do NOT suppress CRITICAL or HIGH CVEs without MLRO/Security team sign-off.
# This file is tracked in git; any addition requires a PR review.
#
# Format: <CVE-ID>  # <package>: <justification>

# GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93  # postcss <8.5.10: XSS via unescaped </style> in CSS stringify output
# Affects next@16.x internal postcss (8.4.31). postcss is a build-time CSS processing
# tool — its stringify output is never served directly to browsers in our Netlify/Docker
# deployment. The XSS vector requires serving raw postcss output as HTML, which we do not
# do. No upstream fix in Next.js available; waiting for next to bundle postcss >=8.5.10.
# Review date: 2026-05-28 | Reviewer: Security team | Next review: 2027-05-28
GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93

# GHSA-w5hq-g745-h8pq  # uuid <11.1.1: Missing buffer bounds check in v3/v5/v6
# Affects exceljs transitive dependency (uuid@8.3.2). The vulnerability only triggers
# when uuid functions are called with an explicit `buf` parameter. exceljs uses uuid
# only for generating IDs without a custom buffer — this code path is never exercised.
# Forcing uuid@^11 would require a breaking exceljs API migration (v3→v4 rename).
# Review date: 2026-05-28 | Reviewer: Security team | Next review: 2027-05-28
GHSA-w5hq-g745-h8pq

# Note: when upstream fixes land for the above, remove these entries and
# tighten the Trivy CI step to --ignore-unfixed=false with no exceptions.
